    "showPassword": "Show password",
    "hidePassword": "Hide password",
    "termsHtml": "<p class=\"last-updated\">Last updated: February 8, 2026</p><h3>1. Acceptance of Terms</h3><p>By accessing and using 365Soft, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions of use. If you do not agree with these terms, you must not use the Service.</p><h3>2. Service Description</h3><p>365Soft is a property management platform that allows administrators to manage properties, tenants, contracts, payments and maintenance efficiently.</p><h3>3. Account Registration</h3><p>To use the Service, you must create an account by providing accurate and complete information. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account and password.</p><h3>4. Acceptable Use</h3><p>You agree to:</p><ul><li>Use the Service only for lawful purposes</li><li>Not share your account with unauthorized third parties</li><li>Keep your account information up to date</li><li>Not attempt to access unauthorized areas of the system</li><li>Not use the Service for fraudulent or illegal activities</li></ul><h3>5. Intellectual Property</h3><p>All content, features and functionality of the Service are the exclusive property of 365Soft and are protected by intellectual property laws.</p><h3>6. Privacy and Data Security</h3><p>We are committed to protecting your personal information according to our Privacy Policy. We implement technical and organizational security measures to protect your data.</p><h3>7. Limitation of Liability</h3><p>365Soft will not be liable for indirect, incidental, special or consequential damages resulting from the use or inability to use the Service.</p><h3>8. Service Changes</h3><p>We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the Service at any time, with or without prior notice.</p><h3>9. Termination</h3><p>We may suspend or terminate your access to the Service if you violate these terms or for any other reason at our discretion.</p><h3>10. Governing Law</h3><p>These terms are governed by the applicable laws in your jurisdiction.</p><h3>11. Contact</h3><p>For questions about these terms, contact: support@365soft.com</p>",
    "privacyHtml": "<p class=\"last-updated\">Last updated: February 8, 2026</p><h3>1. Introduction</h3><p>At 365Soft, we take user privacy very seriously. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, share and protect your personal information.</p><h3>2. Information We Collect</h3><p>We collect the following information:</p><ul><li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, phone, company name</li><li><strong>Property information:</strong> addresses, property data and contracts</li><li><strong>Tenant information:</strong> contact details and required documentation</li><li><strong>Payment information:</strong> transaction history and payment methods</li><li><strong>Usage data:</strong> how you interact with our Service</li><li><strong>Technical information:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system</li></ul><h3>3. How We Use Your Information</h3><p>We use your information to:</p><ul><li>Provide and maintain the Service</li><li>Process transactions and send related notifications</li><li>Improve and personalize your experience</li><li>Communicate with you about updates and news</li><li>Detect and prevent fraud or abuse of the Service</li><li>Comply with legal obligations</li></ul><h3>4. Sharing Information</h3><p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information with:</p><ul><li><strong>Service providers:</strong> who help us operate the Service</li><li><strong>Legal authorities:</strong> when required by law</li><li><strong>Business partners:</strong> with your explicit consent</li></ul><h3>5. Data Security</h3><p>We implement technical and organizational security measures to protect your information.</p><h3>6. Data Retention</h3><p>We retain your personal information while your account is active or as needed to comply with legal obligations.</p><h3>7. Your Rights</h3><p>You may request access, correction, deletion, objection to processing, data portability or withdrawal of consent.</p><h3>8. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h3><p>We use cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience and analyze Service usage.</p><h3>9. Children's Privacy</h3><p>Our Service is not directed to minors under 18. We do not intentionally collect information from minors.</p><h3>10. Contact</h3><p>For questions or concerns about this policy: privacy@365soft.com</p>",
